### Enforce Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) with Supabase `auth.jwt()`

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/database/postgres/row-level-security.mdx

This RLS policy utilizes `auth.jwt()` to restrict user actions, such as updating profiles, unless they have achieved a specific Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) assurance level (e.g., 'aal2'). This ensures that sensitive operations are only performed by users with a higher level of authentication.

```sql
create policy "Restrict updates."
on profiles
as restrictive
for update
to authenticated using (
  (select auth.jwt()->>'aal') = 'aal2'
);
```

