### Set Supabase MFA Failed Verification Table Permissions (SQL)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/auth-hooks/mfa-verification-hook.mdx

These SQL statements manage access permissions for the `public.mfa_failed_verification_attempts` table. It grants all privileges to the `supabase_auth_admin` role, ensuring administrative control. Concurrently, it revokes all permissions from `authenticated`, `anon`, and `public` roles to restrict unauthorized access to sensitive MFA failure data.

```sql
grant all
  on table public.mfa_failed_verification_attempts
  to supabase_auth_admin;

revoke all
  on table public.mfa_failed_verification_attempts
  from authenticated, anon, public;
```

