### Manage Supabase Phone-Based MFA Challenge and Verification

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2024-08-14-third-party-auth-mfa-phone-send-hooks.mdx

This code snippet illustrates the process of implementing phone-based Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) within a Supabase application. It covers both initiating an MFA challenge by sending an SMS or WhatsApp message to the user and subsequently verifying the code received. Upon successful verification, the user's authentication assurance level (`aal`) in their JSON Web Token (JWT) is upgraded to `aal2`.

```ts
// Send an SMS or WhatsApp message to the user
const { data: { challengeId } } = await supabase.auth.mfa.challenge({
  factorId,
})

// To verify the code received by the user
await supabase.auth.mfa.verify({
  factorId,
  challengeId,
  code: '123456',
})

// The user's `aal` claim in the JWT 
// will be upgraded to aal2
```

