### Enforce Supabase MFA with PostgreSQL Row Level Security Policy

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/auth-mfa.mdx

This SQL snippet demonstrates how to create a restrictive Row Level Security (RLS) policy in PostgreSQL to enforce Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for all authenticated users. The policy checks the `auth.jwt()->>'aal'` claim to ensure that only sessions with an `aal2` (highest assurance level) can access the specified table. This effectively denies access to users who have not completed MFA, overriding other policies.

```sql
create policy "Policy name."
  on table_name
  as restrictive
  to authenticated
  using ((select auth.jwt()->>'aal') = 'aal2');
```

